article.description:
Martin Zeno scored 15 points, hit a
tie-breaking free throw and grabbed a steal in the game's final
seconds to help Texas Tech fight off Texas-El Paso 61-60 Sunday.
article.headline: Zeno's free throw gives Texas Tech one-point win over UTEP
article.linkText: Zeno's free throw gives Texas Tech one-point win over UTEP
article.story: LUBBOCK, Texas (AP) -- Martin Zeno scored 15 points, hit a tie-breaking free throw and grabbed a steal in the game's final seconds to help Texas Tech fight off Texas-El Paso 61-60 Sunday. Zeno broke a 60-60 tie by converting one of two free throws with 1:04 remaining. After UTEP's Jason Williams missed a pair of free throws a second later and Tech's Daryl Dora missed a 3-point attempt, the Miners rebounded, called timeout and set up their final possesion. With the final seconds ticking down, UTEP tried to pass the ball inside to John Tofi, but Zeno broke up the play and grabbed the loose ball. He passed the ball downcourt before he could be fouled as time ran out. Zeno's efforts gave Tech (8-6) its second straight win. Jarrius Jackson scored 14 points and Dior Lowhorn and Terry Martin each scored 13 for the Red Raiders. The Miners (7-4) had erased a 12-point Raider lead in the final 6:08. UTEP cut the lead to five, 58-53, at the 4:01 mark on a baseline jumper by Edgar Moreno. Tofi then made it a 58-56 game when he scored on a drive and drew a foul on Zeno with 2:56 left. After Dora hit two free throws with 2:34 left for a 60-56 lead, the Miners answered with a Tofi free throw that made it 60-57 at the 2:15 mark. On UTEP's next possesion, Tofi's inside shot was blocked by Lowhorn, but the ball bounced to UTEP's Miguel Ayala, who missed a 3-pointer. The Miners rebounded and moved the ball to Brent Murphy, who drained a 3-pointer that made it 60-60 with 90 seconds left. Tofi led the Miners with 15 points. Williams added 14. Tech shook off a slow start, missing its first seven shots, before taking control late in the first half. The Miners led 12-7 with 12 minutes left in the opening half, but Tech, led by a trio of 3-pointers by Martin, eventually took a 31-20 lead one minute before intermission. Tech held a 33-23 lead at halftime.
